/* Early life and education */The source attached explicitly states that pashto was spoken at home while she was proficient in urdu & Hindi. And there's no mention of her being addressed as 'majhli' at home.
/* Early life */Accuracy. Hindkowan community has a distinct ethnic and cultural identity.
/* T */Tarkhan is a turkic tribe,NOT Punjabi.
/* M */Mughal tribe was never a Punjabi. Mughals are Persians settled in Punjab and other North Indian states.
/* C */Chachi redirects to a region near KP, not any caste or sub group.

First: although historically hindkowan community mainly resided in north-western Pak, no source mentions that Hindkowans ever inhibited areas near Pak-Afghan border; and the tribal belt has always been a Pashtun territory historically. Second:"Tribes" mentioned here are Pashtuns who've adopted Hindko as their first language for centuries, hence they're hindko-speaking Pashtuns such as Tareens or Dilazak.

/* Origin */The source provided does not mention that hindkowan is pejorative or that Pashtuns are 'second largest' ethnic group in KP. By all statistics/data Pashtuns are the only majority ethnic group in KP.
/* History */ added vital information that had been omitted by someone earlier. (vandalism).
/* Sikh Empire */ Changed Punjabi army with more accurate description i.e Sikh Khalsa Army. Furthermore, this section requires much improvement in terms of neutrality.
/* Rise of Sikhism */  the rise of Sikhism was during the Mughal era, so why does it have a separate section?
/* Maratha Empire */ The section has been merged with the above section; Maratha  rule overlaps Afghan Durrani Rule
/* Durrani Empire */ RE-structured the article for the purpose of coherence.
/* Durrani Empire */ Added vital information regarding Muslim Durrani Empire, that had been pretty much briefly describes in favor pf Punjabi-Sikh Empire.
/* Durrani Afghans */  Added vital info regarding the Durrani empire

/* Mughal era */  Added crucial informayion regarding a very important part of KP history that had been - very strangely- left out in favor of glorification of Marathas and Sikhs - the non-Pashtun rulers of KP. This info is vital and MUST not be removed to distort history in favor of Sikhs..

/* Ingredients and preparation */In traditional Pashtun(Peshwari/Afghan) style of (Chapli) kebab, garam masala is not added; it is in fact Indian way of making 'Peshwari/Chapal Kebab. It's important that on Wikipedia, the method of making this kebab must be as it is in the traditional Pashtun cuisine. In fact most Pashtun dishes/cuisine do not include garam masala. Pashtun cuisine is usually bland &/or with little spices.

/* Durrani's poetry */Ahmad Shah speaks of Pashtun homeland in general when he makes a reference to Pakhtunkhwa, which means the land of Pukhtuns, not Khyber Pakhtunkhwa in particular. KP name itself popped up in Pakistani political circles a decade ago when politicians from the then NWFP wanted to rename NWFP. Ahmad Shah ruled the entire Pashtun region, hence it is impossible to assume that he would only mention KP and leave swathes of land inhibited by Pashtuns in Balochistan and Afghanistan.
